Initial Verification:
- Verify user identity using security questions or manager confirmation
- Confirm the account username and associated email address
- Check if account is locked or just needs password reset

Account Status Check:
- Check Active Directory / Azure AD for account status
- Review failed login attempts and lockout reason
- Verify account is not disabled or expired

Password Reset:
- Reset password in the appropriate directory service (AD/Azure AD/Google Workspace)
- Generate temporary password meeting complexity requirements
- Set flag to require password change on next login

Account Unlock (if applicable):
- Clear account lockout flag in Active Directory
- Reset lockout counter
- Document reason for lockout

Communication:
- Securely communicate new temporary password to user
- Provide password reset self-service portal link for future use
- Remind user of password policy requirements

Verification:
- Confirm user can successfully log in with new credentials
- Verify user has changed temporary password
- Close ticket with resolution notes
